(20, '2016-12-17 12:48:09', '2016-12-17 12:48:09', 1, 'events', 'Pinnacle in the Community', '', '<div class="mainpanel"><a href="#">Bookwallah</a>\r\n<h3><img style="width: 300px; height: 330px; float: right; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" src="http://www.pinper.com/webroot/media/images/BookWallah.png" alt="Bookwallah" />143 Million. That&rsquo;s the number of orphans in the world.</h3>\r\n<p>Bookwallah believes in improving the lives of orphaned children and the lives around them by opening their world to imagination, fostering creativity, encouraging exploration and promoting innovation within their society, through the power and magic of storybooks.</p>\r\n<p>Founded in 2009 by Seena Jacob and co-founders, G. Riley Mills and Ranjeet Nambiar, the U.S. based 501 c (3) non-profit organization brings hope, happiness, and inspiration to orphan children around the world by distributing storybooks and creating inspiring libraries.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Bookwallah&rsquo;s name comes from the Hindi translation, which means &ldquo;book peddler&rdquo;. Currently, Bookwallah has three core programs:</p>\r\n<p>Bookwallah Book Program: We provide children&rsquo;s books in English and local languages. The books donated in English and local languages are organized in existing bookshelves and reading spaces. This is the Bookwallah Organization&rsquo;s core program.</p>\r\n<p>Bookwallah Reading Rug Program: We create child-friendly, comfortable reading areas for the children within the orphanages, if there is a need or a desire. The relationship between physical space, continued interest in reading and use of imagination are highly correlated.</p>\r\n<p>Bookwallah Reading Services: We provide reading sessions to engage the children in fun reading activities and to help evaluate progress.</p>\r\n<a href="#">Israel Antonio: Triathelete</a>\r\n<p><img style="width: 250px; height: 188px; float: left; margin-right: 15px;" src="http://www.pinper.com/webroot/media/images/antonio_isreal.JPG" alt="Antonio Isreal" />Pinnacle Performance Company sponsors visually impaired athlete and screenwriter Israel Antonio. Antonio, who competes in both half and full marathons and triathlons with the aid of sighted guides, was one of G. Riley Mills&rsquo; students when he taught &ldquo;Playwriting for the Actor&rdquo; at the former Breadline Theater.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Antonio lost his eyesight when he was 14 years old. A childhood athlete and sports fanatic, Antonio participated in limited athletic activities after losing his sight until 2007. He was inspired to get back in shape after hearing interviews with a high profile celebrity trainer and the youngest person to ever compete in the Ironman.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>He searched for adaptive sports and eventually found the C Different Foundation, which inspires blind and visually impaired people to lead active, athletic lifestyles. The organization actively works to create opportunities for visually impaired athletes to participate in athletic events. Antonio is an active member and now helps raise awareness for the organization.</p>\r\n<p><img style="width: 175px; height: 264px; float: right; margin-left: 15px;" src="http://www.pinper.com/webroot/media/images/antonio_isreal_2.jpg" alt="Triathelete" />Antonio set a personal best time in the Houston Half Marathon in 2013 and was crowned the 2013 USA Paratriathlon National Champion (Male TRI-6A) at the CapTexTri in Austin, TX, which hosted the Paratriathlon National event, and finished 10th in the 2013 Paratriathlon World Competition held in London.</p>\r\n<a href="#">Ronald McDonald House</a>\r\n<p><img style="width: 200px; height: 343px; float: right; margin-left: 15px;" src="http://www.pinper.com/webroot/media/images/rmhc_logo_color.png" alt="Ronald McDonald\'s House" />Ronald McDonald House&rsquo;s mission is to care for families of children with complex medical needs by providing comfort, compassion and community. &nbsp;RMHC-CNI keeps families of hospitalized children together in a &lsquo;home away from home&rsquo;.</p>\r\n<p>Located near Advocate Children&rsquo;s Hospital, Loyola University Medical Center, University of Chicago Comer Children&rsquo;s Hospital, and the new Ann &amp; Robert H. Lurie Children&rsquo;s Hospital of Chicago, the Houses allow families to eat, sleep and find the emotional support they need - just blocks from where their child is being treated. In 2012, the organization provided over 30,000 nights to families, offering them care and comfort during their hours of greatest need. While they suggest a donation of $10 per night, no family is ever turned away if they are unable to pay.</p>\r\n<p>David Lewis, Pinnacle&rsquo;s cofounder and CEO, is an active board member and recently organized a Performance-Based Communication skills training session for employees and volunteers to improve how they communicate with families, donors and sponsors.</p>\r\n</div>', '1', 'en'),
(21, '2016-12-17 12:51:31', '2016-12-19 09:40:32', 1, 'events', 'Red Carpet Archives', '', '<div class="mainpanel">\r\n<h2>Red Carpet Archives</h2>\r\n<a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="312" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">Introducing The Pinnacle Podcast</a> <strong>May 31, 2016</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="272" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">How DO You Lead A Horse To Water?</a> <strong>February 27, 2014</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="271" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">An Interview With Israel Antonio, US Para-triathlete Champion</a> <strong>February 23, 2014</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="269" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">Lost In Thought</a> <strong>December 11, 2013</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="239" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">In The Eye Of The Beholder: How Perception Of Stress Is Reality</a> <strong>September 12, 2013</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="235" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">Hold Em Or Fold Em?</a> <strong>July 28, 2013</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="231" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">A Good Rule Of Um</a> <strong>May 21, 2013</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="230" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">E-nough Is Enough</a> <strong>March 20, 2013</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="229" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">An Interview With Karen Jaw-Madson</a> <strong>March 19, 2013</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="228" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">When In Rome...</a> <strong>January 29, 2013</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="225" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">The Eyes Have It</a> <strong>November 16, 2012</strong> <a class="get-post" href="#" data-id="217" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">Jung At Heart, Or Not</a> <strong>September 6, 2012</strong> <a class="get-