(62, '2016-12-19 09:34:39', '2016-12-19 09:34:39', 1, 'events-tab', 'Active Listening Goes - Up In The Air', 'Red Carpet Archives', '<p><strong>Fact Check:</strong> According to experts, ____ % of everything we learn is learned through listening. On average, a person retains and remembers about ____ % of what they hear.</p>\r\n<p>(Read on for Answers)</p>\r\n<p>What is Active Listening...</p>\r\n<p>Communication is a two-way street between a speaker and their audience. Active listening is the foundation of effective communication and a way for an audience to take in information and respond to a speaker. It\'s much more than simply making eye contact.</p>\r\n<p><em>We have two ears and one mouth so we can listen twice as much as we speak.</em><em><br /></em><em>-Epictetus</em></p>\r\n<p>Why Active Listening...</p>\r\n<p>It can allow for and improve mutual understanding between two parties. As a speaker, you can receive immediate visual feedback from your audience simply by looking at them and interacting with them in verbal and non-verbal ways. Success and failure of this technique can both be seen in the new Golden Globe nominated movie, Up in the Air. The success of George Clooney\'s character, Ryan Bingham, is predicated on active listening. Bingham fires people for a living. To be successful he must focus on their reactions and their needs before he responds. He utilizes active listening. The new girl on the block, Anna Kendrick\'s Natalie Keener, is far less skilled in this area. Instead of listening she allows her own opinions to impede her interviews. Natalie misses cues, does not ask pertinent questions, and is ultimately ineffective because of her inflexibility. Ryan\'s approach yields much more favorable results. Up in the Air is entertaining, poignant and contains a series of great examples of active listening. This places it amongst Pinnacle\'s top 10 movies for 2009.</p>\r\n<p>Tips for Active Listening</p>\r\n<p>It\'s easy to talk about the process and fun to see our favorite actors do it in the movies, but to help you focus on the details, here are some tips to help practice active listening and keep it at the forefront of your mind.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Be other directed - have empathy for the speaker</li>\r\n<li>Acknowledge your emotional state and set aside opinions</li>\r\n<li>Focus on the subject</li>\r\n<li>Avoid distractions</li>\r\n<li>Ask questions</li>\r\n<li>Take notes</li>\r\n<li>Use nonverbal communication</li>\r\n<li>Paraphrase what you have heard</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Keep these handy, especially before an important interaction to remind yourself to focus not just on your message but on the audience.</p>\r\n<p>Some other great movies featuring examples of active listening:</p>\r\n<div>The Informant<br />The Hurt Locker</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Fact Check Answers: According to experts, 80% of everything we learn is learned through listening. On average, a person retains and remembers about 20% of what they hear.</em></strong><em><br /></em></p>', '1', 'en'),
(63, '2016-12-19 12:07:05', '2016-12-19 12:07:05', 1, 'company-tab', 'David Lewis', 'Leadership', '<p>David is <strong>Co-Founder and CEO of Pinnacle Performance Company</strong>, a global, training firm that has revolutionized presentation and communication skills training. He is also co-inventor of The Pinnacle MethodTM, a unique and innovative learning system that meshes time-tested performance delivery techniques with contemporary business skills.</p>\r\n<p>Prior to launching Pinnacle, David spent a number of years in executive level sales and marketing positions at Fortune 500 companies and hi-tech/internet start-ups. He is an accomplished actor / producer, and is also a member of the Screen Actors Guild with a number of stage, film and commercial credits.</p>\r\n<p>David is an internationally sought-after speaker, having delivered keynote addresses for several organizations &amp; institutions in countless industries around the world. David and co-founder G. Riley Mills have written the acclaimed book based on the award-winning Pinnacle Method, The Pin Drop Principle.</p>\r\n<p>David lives in Chicago where he proudly serves on the Board of Directors for Ronald McDonald House Charities.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(64, '2016-12-19 12:18:05', '2016-12-19 12:18:05', 1, 'company-tab', 'G. Riley Mills', 'Leadership', '<p>G. Riley Mills is the co-founder of Pinnacle Performance Company and co-author of <em id="yiv4321974792yui_3_16_0_1_1416616834564_2656">The Pin Drop Principle. </em>He&nbsp;has taught effective communication to executives and CEOs in over 30 countries across the globe. Mills has guest-lectured or delivered keynotes at such events and institutions as Columbia University, Association of Training and Development (national conference), London Chamber of Commerce, New York University, Young Presidents\' Organization, Cox School of Business, Southern Methodist University, Learning and Skills Conference (London), SHRM (regional chapters), Singapore Management University and Manchester United.</p>\r\n<p>As a writer, Mills has twice been awarded the Joseph Jefferson Citation for Best New Work.&nbsp;His first book, <em>Sawdust and Spangles </em>(written with Grammy-nominated musician Ralph Covert) won a 2007 NAPPA Honor Award and their follow-up project, <em>A Nutty Nutcracker Christmas</em> was profiled in <em>USA Today</em> and on ABC&rsquo;s &ldquo;Nightline&rdquo;. In 2012, their acclaimed musical, <em id="yiv4321974792yui_3_16_0_1_1416616834564_2801">The Hundred Dresses</em>, premiered Off-Broadway at the Atlantic Theatre Company in New York City and was nominated for a 2013 Distinguished Play Award. Mills\' writing has also appeared in <em>Fast Company.</em></p>\r\n<p>As an actor, he appeared on &ldquo;ER&rdquo;, &ldquo;Early Edition&rdquo; and the movie <em id="yiv4321974792yui_3_16_0_1_1416616834564_2804">35 Miles From Normal</em>, which premiered at the 1997 Sundance Film Festival.&nbsp;A member of the Screen Actors Guild, Mills co-founded a not-for-profit company called The Bookwallah Organization, whose sole mission is to collect storybooks, set up libraries and promote literacy in orphanages around the world (<a href="http://www.bookwallah.org">www.bookwallah.org</a>).&nbsp;</p>', '1', 'en'),
(65, '2016-12-19 12:20:48', '2016-12-19 12:20:48', 1, 'company-tab', 'Gerri Leon', 'Leadership', '<p>With well over 20 years of design and marketing experience, Gerri has contributed to the brand building and global marketing initiatives of global technology, biotech and medical diagnostic companies and now serves as Pinnacle&rsquo;s Vice President for Marketing. She has developed advertising campaigns, marketing collateral, multimedia and architectural design projects for many products. Gerri started as a designer but learned early on that she had a talent, not only for creativity, but for marrying it with the analytical process side of business. Out of this she has developed a specialization in integrated marketing communications and operations.</p>\r\n<p>As a community volunteer, Gerri volunteers with Junior Achievement teaching high school students success skills, the American Red Cross working on the coordination of events in support of the New Mexico Champions and Real Heroes Campaigns and is the VP of Communications for the New Mexico chapter of the American Marketing Association Board of Directors.</p>\r\n<p>Gerri studied graphic design at California Institute of the Arts in Valencia, California, and received a BA in psychology from the University of California at Los Angeles and an MBA from San Diego State University.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(66, '2016-12-19 12:23:23', '2016-12-19 12:23:23', 1, 'company-tab', 'Brian McNeany', 'Leadership', '<p>Brian is the Vice President of sales for Pinnacle Performance Company. Brian has over 16 years of corporate experience, beginning his career with Andersen Consulting (Accenture). He has held a variety of leadership roles, including product manager, business development executive, call center director and vice president of global partnerships. Past clients include American Express, Comcast, John Hancock, Banana Republic, Sears and Qualcomm, among others.</p>\r\n<p>As an actor, Brian has spent time in both New York and Los Angeles. His film work includes the major motion pictures <em>Pleasantville</em> and <em>Mystic River</em>, as well as the lead role in the independent film <em>The Return</em>. On TV he has appeared on <em>Guiding Light</em> and <em>The Big Date</em> and was featured in a VH1 holiday commercial. Brian\'s stage credits include <em>Proof</em>, <em>Who\'s Afraid of Virginia Woolf?</em>, <em>The Boys Next Door</em>, <em>To Forgive Divine</em> and <em>Orphans</em>.</p>\r\n<p>Brian received his bachelor degree from Worcester Polytechnic Institute and has studied acting at Michael Howard Studios, C.P. Casting, and The Harrison Project.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(67, '2016-12-19 12:24:53', '2016-12-19 12:24:53', 1, 'company-tab', 'Tim Kasper', 'Leadership', '<p>Emmy award-winning Tim Kasper is the Vice President for Southeast Region of Pinnacle Performance Company. As an artist, he has been performing since the age of 13. He received much of his early training at the prestigious Trollwood Performing Arts School and under the tutelage of Broadway veterans Eddie and Kathy Gasper. While an advertising major at the University of St. Thomas in St. Paul MN, his love of performing called him back to tour with his vocal band, The Blenders (<a href="http://www.theblenders.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.theblenders.com</a>). They&rsquo;ve been together since 1990 and are still going strong.</p>\r\n<p>The Blenders have toured all over the U.S. and have been the favorite opening act for Howie Mandel and Jay Leno at Caesars Palace and MGM Grand in Las Vegas and Caesars Atlantic City. Their 11 CD titles have sold a quarter of a million units, with a #1 hit single in Europe.</p>\r\n<p>Tim has stayed busy with acting and print modeling for companies such as Best Buy and John Deere. He co-hosted a movie-review radio show called &ldquo;The Reel Brothers&rdquo; in Minneapolis for three years with his brother, Patrick. He also co-hosted a television show on the Minneapolis/St. Paul FOX affiliate called &ldquo;Minnesota Spotlight.&rdquo; His teaching credits include various performing arts and dance schools in the Midwest and Florida, along with teaching master-classes at Minnesota State University-Moorhead and the Ringling school of Art and Design, Sarasota Florida.</p>\r\n<p>Tim is a member of the American Federation of Television and Radio Artists and is active in the Young Professionals Group in Sarasota, Florida.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(68, '2016-12-19 12:26:01', '2016-12-19 12:26:01', 1, 'company-tab', 'Cindy Tegtmeyer', 'Leadership', '<p>Cindy Tegtmeyer brings a unique combination of business, teaching and performance skills to her role as Pinnacle&rsquo;s Director of U.S. Client Relations.</p>\r\n<p>She has served as Production Consultant for Chicago&rsquo;s hit show, The Magic Cabaret, Vice President for Clean Customized Comedy, a corporate entertainment company, and Managing Director of the Actors&rsquo; Center of Chicago. She has spent the past 20 years implementing numerable artist residency programs, and, as a standardized patient, Cindy teaches communication skills to medical students at The Clinical Education Center at Northwestern University&rsquo;s Feinberg School of Medicine.</p>\r\n<p>Cindy\'s professional performing resume spans 15 years, both in Chicago and across the country. Her list of roles includes two years touring and at The Royal George Theatre in Leaving Iowa (Sis), The Rabbit Hole (Izzy) with Buffalo Theatre Ensemble and even a year as a clown with Ringling Bros. Barnum &amp; Bailey Circus.</p>\r\n<p>As a voice-over artist and member of SAG (Screen Actors Guild) and AFTRA (American Federation of Television and Radio Artists), Cindy has voiced over 300 radio and TV commercials for clients such as McDonalds, Ford, Sears, Hallmark, Sprint, Anheuser-Busch and Kelloggs. She has also provided live international industrial services for Philip Morris and Gap.</p>\r\n<p>Cindy possesses a Bachelor of Fine Arts from Millikin University.</p>', '1', 'en');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `category_id`, `alias`, `title`, `subtitle`, `content`, `visible`, `lang`) VALUES
(69, '2016-12-19 12:27:43', '2016-12-19 12:27:43', 1, 'company-tab', 'Rob Lynch', 'Leadership', '<p>Prior to working with Pinnacle, Rob spent 14 years in the public relations industry publicizing clients for large global agencies like Porter Novelli, Burson-Marsteller and Ketchum and small creative boutiques like EBS Public Relations and Dome Communications. He also handled all of public relations activities for TransUnion&rsquo;s business-to-business divisions. Rob has appeared in commercials for The Chicago White Sox and Harris Bank and is one of the featured faces for The Chicago White Sox&rsquo; &ldquo;All In&rdquo; advertising print campaign.<br /> He has performed throughout Chicago with two independent improv teams, Mix 7 and Old Dogs. He also has performed for theater companies across Los Angeles and the Chicagoland area, including Chemically Imbalanced Comedy, Red Tape Theatre, Sideshow Theatre Company, The Raven Theatre, Side Project Theatre Company and the Bailiwick. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /> Rob has a Bachelor of Science degree in public relations from Loras College in Dubuque, IA. He has completed the Meisner program at Act One Studios and improv training programs at Second City, iO (formerly improve Olympic) and the Annoyance. He currently resides in Los Angeles, CA.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(70, '2016-12-19 12:28:58', '2016-12-19 12:28:58', 1, 'company-tab', 'Brad Lawrence', 'Leadership', '<p>Brad Lawrence is the Editorial Director for Pinnacle&rsquo;s newsletters, website and curriculum. As the former managing director of the Actors&rsquo; Center Chicago and an accomplished stage/screen actor and playwright Brad brings an immense amount of talent and expertise to his role. Brad&rsquo;s acting resume features principal roles from contemporary, classical and musical genres. He has appeared in many commercials, films, industrials and on stages around Chicago, most notably with the Goodman, About Face and Buffalo Theatre Ensemble.</p>\r\n<p>In 2001 Brad co-founded Odyssey Express, a professional children&rsquo;s touring theatre that performed educational and entertaining programs for schools and libraries in Chicago and the surrounding suburbs. His most recent show, an operetta of Rudyard Kipling&rsquo;s <em>The Jungle Book</em>, is currently touring the Chicagoland area. Brad&rsquo;s other plays have been produced by a variety of venues around the city, including the Chicago Cultural Center and the Breadline, Bailiwick and Metropolis Centers for the Performing Arts. In 2006 he was selected as a semifinalist in the Goodman Theatre&rsquo;s David Mamet Speakeasy contest.<br /> <br /> As an adjunct faculty member he recently directed a production of <em>Agnes of God </em>for the College of DuPage and intends to continue teaching collegiately in addition to his Pinnacle responsibilities. Brad holds an M.F.A. in acting from Western Illinois University, where he also taught acting, Shakespeare and theatre studies.<br /> <br /> Brad is also one of&nbsp; Pinnacle&rsquo;s Master Instructors, having been with the company since its inception in 2004. Like many professional artists, Brad has worn a variety of hats over the years, and is always looking for new ways to wed his creative experiences with his work for Pinnacle.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(71, '2016-12-20 07:26:27', '2016-12-20 07:48:38', 5, 'vcoach', 'Benefits', 'left-block', '<h1>Benefits</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Learn how to be a more <strong>compelling</strong> credible and confident communicator.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Improve</strong> the retention and reception of your message.</li>\r\n<li>Get coaching when you need it from the <strong>convenience</strong> of your home or office.</li>\r\n<li>Be <strong>better prepared</strong> for even last minute meetings and presentations with express service.</li>\r\n</ul>', '1', 'en'),
(72, '2016-12-20 07:30:53', '2016-12-20 07:48:26', 5, 'vcoach', 'IS VIRTUAL COACH FOR YOU?', 'center-block', '<p>Pinnacle\'s highly trained master instructors are now available without you having to leave your home or office.</p>\r\n<p>With experience coaching individuals at all levels, from start-ups to the Fortune 100, Pinnacle\'s trainers can help put that extra polish on your next presentation or speaking engagement.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(73, '2016-12-20 07:31:50', '2016-12-20 08:30:59', 5, 'vcoach', 'WHAT DOES IT COST & WHAT DO I GET?', 'right-block', '<h2>What does it cost &amp; what do I get?</h2>\r\n<p>Pinnacle Performance Company&rsquo;s Virtual Coach weds the convenience of modern technology with our innovative approach to communication. Check out the Prices page for detailed pricing. Whatever your next moment in the spotlight may be, Virtual Coach enables you to harness the professional power of the Pinnacle Method wherever and whenever you need it.</p>\r\n<p><a href="assets/dist/cms/pdf/sample_report.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Click here to view a sample report</a></p>', '1', 'en'),
(74, '2016-12-20 09:32:34', '2016-12-20 09:32:34', 5, 'about', 'TESTIMONIAL', 'left-block', '<h3 class="text-center">TESTIMONIAL</h3>\r\n<p><em>"[Pinnacle] provided a detailed individual performance report to each of our global rising leaders. This was an excellent virtual coaching approach and the outcome was well worth the investment."</em></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Fei Sun</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Accenture &ndash; Global Leadership Development</em></p>', '1', 'en'),
(75, '2016-12-20 09:36:01', '2016-12-20 09:36:01', 5, 'about', 'About Us', 'right-block', '<h2>ABOUT US</h2>\r\n<h3>pinnacle Performance Company</h3>\r\n<p>Pinnacle Performance Company is an award-winning global communication skills training company that was created by meshing critical business communication skills with time honored acting techniques.</p>\r\n<p>Whether you are in the C-Suite or the New-Suite, The Pinnacle Method&trade; teaches you how to understand the objective and intention of your message. Whether communicating to a single individual or a large audience, our innovative apporach to delivery skills will ensure your audience reacts the way you want.</p>\r\n<p>Please visit www.pinper.com to better understand our competitive differentiators, our customized modules and our unique approach.</p>\r\n<h3>pinnacle Master Trainers</h3>\r\n<p>The Pinnacle team includes some of the most dynamic and experienced trainers working in the industry today. With a blend of performance and corporate expertise, they are the best at what they do: Intention-Based Training.</p>\r\n<p>All Pinnacle instructors across the globe are certified in the Pinnacle Method and train exclusively with Pinnacle. They undergo rigorous training before they become certified and are required to be re-certified every year in order to continue teaching the Pinnacle Method.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(76, '2016-12-20 10:15:21', '2016-12-20 10:15:21', 5, 'features', 'Secure and Private', 'center-block', '<h1>Features</h1>\r\n<h3>Secure and Private</h3>\r\n<p>Once you create your account, your videos and coaching materials are stored on our secure server. This safeguards your privacy and ensures a safe environment in which to make payments and receive feedback.</p>\r\n<h3>Convenient</h3>\r\n<p>Receive professional feedback and guidance when and where YOU need it. Record and upload your video from the convenience of your home or office whenever you like. No schedules. No appointments. No hassle.</p>\r\n<h3>Affordable</h3>\r\n<p>Less expensive than on-site personal coaching or group sessions that you need to book in advance. Tiered pricing and customizable extras guarantee you&rsquo;ll find the right package for you and your pocketbook.</p>\r\n<h3>Trained, Experienced Professionals</h3>\r\n<p>Pinnacle\'s Master Coaches are certified by Pinnacle through its rigorous training and certification program. Our personnel all have extensive global experience with companies of all sizes and individuals of all skill levels.</p>\r\n<h3>Extras</h3>\r\n<p>Along with your paid product selection you will be given year-long access to our exclusive Pinnacle Learning Portal. An ever-increasing library of tools and information will be at your fingertips to continue your improvement and enhance your skills.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(77, '2016-12-20 13:01:32', '2016-12-20 13:19:08', 5, 'how-it-works', 'create a video', 'video', '<p>Using your computer\'s webcam or other video recording device, record five minutes of your speech or presentation. Don&rsquo;t worry about it being perfect, and there&rsquo;s no need for editing. The raw footage will do fine. The most important thing is that you feel it is generally representative of you and your delivery style.</p>\r\n<p>Click <a href="#">here</a> for guidance on set up, format and file requirements for your video.</p>\r\n<p>After you setup your video camera, webcam, smartphone or other recording device to record your video, don\'t forget the following:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Relax.</strong> Don&rsquo;t worry about shooting something worthy of Hollywood. The most important thing is that your video be representative of your delivery style.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Video Length.</strong> Please keep your video between four and five minutes. This will give your coach enough material to analyze without making it cumbersome to upload.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Framing.</strong> Your virtual coach will want to see as much of you as possible for feedback purposes. Aim for &frac34; of your body to be visible and no less than &frac12;.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Lighting.</strong> Record in a well-illuminated environment. Too bright is better than too dark. Try to avoid exclusively top-down lighting, as it will cast shadows on your face and make your expressions difficult to read.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Wardrobe.</strong> Wear something similar to what you would be wearing while delivering your chosen material. Clothing affects movement and comfortability, and it\'s important for your coach to get a sense of both.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sound.</strong> Do your best to eliminate ambient noise. Record at a time and in a place where background distractions are minimal.</p>\r\n<p>If you have any technical questions, please see our <a href="../../vcoach/faqs">FAQ</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks and have fun!</p>', '1', 'en'),
(78, '2016-12-20 13:02:18', '2016-12-20 13:18:48', 5, 'how-it-works', 'upload your video', 'upload', '<ol>\r\n<li>Upload your video to Pinnacle&rsquo;s secure server.</li>\r\n<li>Complete the payment process.</li>\r\n<li>A Pinnacle Master Coach will be assigned to you, and you will receive his/her profile and further details via email.</li>\r\n</ol>', '1', 'en'),
(79, '2016-12-20 13:03:03', '2016-12-20 13:18:17', 5, 'how-it-works', 'receive coaching', 'coaching', '<ol>\r\n<li>Your personal coach will review your video and provide a detailed action plan you can immediately put to work for improved communication and presentation skills.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in a 45 Minute live coaching session with your master coach to review your personal video or to delve into specific communication and presentation skills topics you want help with.</li>\r\n<li>Continue to take advantage of the resources available in the Learning Portal, your personal customer portal.</li>\r\n</ol>', '1', 'en'),
(80, '2016-12-20 13:03:43', '2016-12-20 13:17:52', 5, 'how-it-works', 'succeed', 'succeed', '<p>Take your new tools and give the performance of a lifetime!</p>', '1', 'en'),
(81, '2016-12-20 13:47:34', '2016-12-20 13:47:34', 5, 'faqs', 'I have uploaded my video, but I have not received notification that my Master Coach has been assigned.', '', '<p>First, check your spam folder as occasionally these notifications get filtered by spam and junk mail filters. Alternatively, you can log into your Virtual Coach Customer Portal and view who has been assigned as your coach, as well as see their profile.</p>\r\n<p>If you log in and do not see your coach&rsquo;s profile, make sure you completed your checkout. After you upload your video, you need to complete the purchase process before a coach will be assigned.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(82, '2016-12-20 13:48:07', '2016-12-20 13:48:07', 5, 'faqs', 'How long does it take to receive my personalized report from my Master Coach?', '', '<p>The standard turnaround time is two to five days. Generally our master coaches will complete within the two days.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(83, '2016-12-20 13:48:44', '2016-12-20 13:48:44', 5, 'faqs', 'Who will be reviewing my video and providing my custom report?', '', '<p>The Pinnacle team of Master Coaches includes some of the most dynamic and experienced trainers working in the industry today. With a blend of performance and corporate expertise, they are the best at what they do: Intention-Based Training.</p>\r\n<p>All Pinnacle instructors across the globe are certified in the Pinnacle Method and train exclusively with Pinnacle. They undergo rigorous training before they become certified and are required to be re-certified every year in order to continue teaching the Pinnacle Method.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(84, '2016-12-20 13:49:21', '2016-12-20 13:49:21', 5, 'faqs', 'How to record a video', '', '<p>After you setup your video camera, webcam, smartphone or other recording device to record your video, don\'t forget the following:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Relax. </strong>Don&rsquo;t worry about shooting something worthy of Hollywood. The most important thing is that your video be representative of your delivery style.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Video Length. </strong>Please keep your video between four and five minutes. This will give your coach enough material to analyze without making it cumbersome to upload.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Framing. </strong>Your virtual coach will want to see as much of you as possible for feedback purposes. Aim for &frac34; of your body to be visible and no less than &frac12;.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Lighting.</strong> Record in a well illuminated environment. Too bright is better than too dark. Avoid exclusively top-down lighting, as it will cast shadows on your face and make your expressions difficult to read.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Wardrobe.</strong> Wear something similar to what you would be wearing while delivering your chosen material. Clothing affects movement and comfortability, and it\'s important for your coach to get a sense of both.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sound.</strong> Do your best to eliminate ambient noise. Record at a time and in a place where background distractions are minimal.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(85, '2016-12-20 13:50:17', '2016-12-20 13:50:17', 5, 'faqs', 'What video formats do you accept?', '', '<p>Virtual Coach accepts most modern recording formats. Here is our complete list:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>.MP4 (most compatible)</li>\r\n<li>.MOV</li>\r\n<li>.MPEG4</li>\r\n<li>.MPG</li>\r\n<li>.AVI</li>\r\n<li>.WMV</li>\r\n<li>.3GP</li>\r\n<li>.FLV (flash video)</li>\r\n<li>.WebM</li>\r\n</ul>', '1', 'en'),
(86, '2016-12-20 13:51:09', '2016-12-20 13:51:09', 5, 'faqs', 'What if my video is not in one of your listed formats?', '', '<p>You will have to convert it to a format Virtual Coach accepts. There are a variety of freeware video converters available on the internet.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(87, '2016-12-20 13:51:47', '2016-12-20 13:51:47', 5, 'faqs', 'Should I (not) shoot in widescreen?', '', '<p>Virtual Coach accepts aspect ratios from 9:16 to 16:9. Anything outside this range will not upload properly. Most recording devices shoot in either 4:3 standard or 16:9 widescreen, so you should be okay.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(88, '2016-12-20 13:52:21', '2016-12-20 13:52:21', 5, 'faqs', 'Should I (not) shoot in HD?', '', '<p>Once your video is uploaded, its quality will degrade slightly. High definition video will retain its quality better than standard definition, but the difference is negligible. Feel free to use either.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(89, '2016-12-20 13:53:25', '2016-12-20 13:53:25', 5, 'faqs', 'I’ve uploaded my video, but there’s no sound. Why?', '', '<p>Virtual Coach probably doesn&rsquo;t support your audio codec. Listed below are our supported video formats and the audio codecs that pair best with them.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>.MP4 - AAC audio</li>\r\n<li>.MOV - AAC audio</li>\r\n<li>.MPEG4 - AAC audio</li>\r\n<li>.AVI - PCM audio</li>\r\n<li>.WMV - WMA audio</li>\r\n<li>.3GP - AAC audio</li>\r\n<li>.FLV (flash video) - MP3 audio</li>\r\n<li>.WebM - Vorbis audio</li>\r\n</ul>', '1', 'en'),
(90, '2016-12-20 13:54:15', '2016-12-20 13:54:15', 5, 'faqs', 'What frame rate should I use when shooting?', '', '<p>Most devices will default to something acceptable. Virtual Coach&rsquo;s maximum is 30fps (frames per second). If your video&rsquo;s frame rate is variable, Virtual Coach will average it. If it is undetermined, VC will use 30fps.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(91, '2016-12-20 13:55:21', '2016-12-20 13:55:21', 5, 'faqs', 'How many audio channels should I use?', '', '<p>Virtual Coach will maintain stereo and mono audio streams. 5.1 channel audio will be down-mixed to stereo. All other channel configurations are unsupported.</p>', '1', 'en'),
(92, '2016-12-20 13:56:34', '2016-12-20 13:56:34', 5, 'faqs', 'What will the report look like?', '', '<p><a href="assets/dist/cms/pdf/sample_report.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Click here to view a sample</a></p>', '1', 'en'),
(93, '2016-12-20 13:57:35', '2016-12-20 14:02:00', 5, 'faqs', 'What are the compatible browsers for Virtual Coach?', '', '<p>The site should be compatible with most browsers. Below are the browsers we recommend.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Internet Explorer 9 (recommended), 8 &amp; 7</li>\r\n<li>Firefox 4 &amp; above</li>\r\n<li>Google Chrome 10 &amp; above</li>\r\n<li>Safari 4 &amp; above</li>\r\n<li>Opera</li>\r\n</ul>', '1', 'en'),
(94, '2016-12-20 14:16:09', '2016-12-20 14:16:09', 5, 'terms', 'terms', '', '<p><strong>1. Your Acceptance</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>By using or visiting the Pinnacle Performance Company&rsquo;s Virtual Coach you signify your agreement to these terms and conditions (the "Terms of Service").</li>\r\n<li>Although we may attempt to notify you when major changes are made to these Terms of Service, you should periodically review the most up-to-date version. Pinnacle Performance Company may, in its sole discretion, modify or revise these Terms of Service and policies at any time, and you agree to be bound by such modifications or revisions. Nothing in these Terms of Service shall be deemed to confer any third-party rights or benefits.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>2. Service</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>These Terms of Service apply to all users of the Service. &ldquo;Content&rdquo; includes the documents, videos, audiovisual combinations, interactive features and other materials you may view on, access through, or contribute to the Service. The Service includes all aspects of Virtual Coach, including but not limited to all products and services offered via the Pinnacle Performance Company website.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>3. Virtual Coach Accounts</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>In order to access the features of the Service, you will have to create a Virtual Coach account. By agreeing to the terms of this agreement, you are obligated to use only your account and agree not to share your account information with others.&nbsp; When creating your account, you must provide accurate and complete information. You are solely responsible for the activity that occurs on your account, and you must keep your account password secure. You must notify Pinnacle Performance Company immediately of any breach of security or unauthorized use of your account.</li>\r\n<li>Although Pinnacle Performance Company will not be liable for your losses caused by any unauthorized use of your account, you